<h4 style="text-align: left; font-size: 12pt; margin-top: 6.00pt; margin-bottom: 2.00pt;"><b><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 18pt; font-weight: bold;" face="Arial"
	 size="5">Relation Description</font></b></h4>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;">&#160;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;"><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;" face="Arial" size="2">Relations
 provide a way of linking one multiple record or item to one or more multiple
 records or items. For example, suppose a questionnaire contains two record
 types, child records and mother records. Each child record contains a
 data item that gives the sequence number of the mother record of the child's
 mother. A relation can be defined which links child records to mother
 records so that when data items from a child record are processes, the
 corresponding mother record data items are available for processing. Relations
 work much like database joins.</font></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;">&#160;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;"><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;" face="Arial" size="2">Relations
 have one primary multiple record or item. Each instance of the primary
 element in a case is processed one at a time. A relation has one or more
 secondary records or items. The corresponding secondary elements are linked
 to the primary element during processing.</font></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;">&#160;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;"><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;" face="Arial" size="2">There
 are four types of linking that can defined by relations.</font></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;">&#160;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-left: 18.00pt; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;
	 text-indent: -18.00pt;"><b><font style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;
										 font-weight: bold;" face="Arial"
										 size="2">Occurrence to Occurrence</font></b>
 <font style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;" face="Arial" size="2">â€“
 Corresponding occurrences of the primary record or item and secondary
 record or item are linked, that is first occurrences are linked, second
 occurrences are linked and so on.</font></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;">&#160;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-left: 18.00pt; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;
	 text-indent: -18.00pt;"><b><font style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;
										 font-weight: bold;" face="Arial"
										 size="2">Item to Occurrence</font></b>
 <font style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;" face="Arial" size="2">â€“
 The value of an item on the primary record is a pointer to the occurrence
 of the secondary record.</font></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;">&#160;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-left: 18.00pt; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;
	 text-indent: -18.00pt;"><b><font style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;
										 font-weight: bold;" face="Arial"
										 size="2">Occurrence to Item</font></b>
 <font style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;" face="Arial" size="2">â€“
 The value of an item on the secondary record is a pointer to the occurrence
 of the primary record.</font></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;">&#160;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-left: 18.00pt; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;
	 text-indent: -18.00pt;"><b><font style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;
										 font-weight: bold;" face="Arial"
										 size="2">Item to Item</font></b>
 <font style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;" face="Arial" size="2">â€“
 The value of an item on the primary record is compared to the value of
 an item on the secondary record. If the values are equal, the records
 are linked.</font></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;">&#160;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;"><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;" face="Arial" size="2">Relations
 can be used in</font> <b><font style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;
								 font-weight: bold;" face="Arial" size="2">for</font></b>
 <font style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;" face="Arial" size="2">statements
 in batch programs and in the Export Data tool.</font></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;">&#160;</p>
